# Supabase Auth — Configuration Reference

---

## First-Day Settings (configure before first user signs up)

```
Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Settings (Providers) → Email

Key settings to configure on every new project:

1. Confirm email: ON for production, OFF for development
   → OFF = users can sign in immediately without confirming email
   → Always turn ON before going to production

2. Secure password change: ON (always)
   → Requires users to re-verify old email before changing to new email
   → Prevents account takeover via email change

3. Double confirm changes: ON (recommended)
   → Both old and new email must confirm before email address changes
   → Without this: user can change email to attacker's email silently

4. Enable sign-ups: ON for open beta, OFF for closed beta or post-launch
   → Dashboard → Auth → Settings → User Signups → Disable sign-ups
   → Existing users can still sign in; new registrations rejected

5. JWT expiry: 3600 (1hr default)
   → Lower = more secure but more network calls for refresh
   → 300 (5min) for high-security apps
   → Never set below 60 seconds (causes UI flicker from constant refresh)
```

