## Email Templates — Variables and Common Bugs

All template variables use Go template syntax: `{{ .VariableName }}`

```
Dashboard → Auth → Email Templates

Available variables:
  {{ .ConfirmationURL }}  — full confirmation link (for confirm, invite, recovery)
  {{ .Token }}            — 6-digit OTP code (for OTP/magic link flows)
  {{ .TokenHash }}        — hashed token (for custom redirect implementations)
  {{ .SiteURL }}          — your site URL from auth settings
  {{ .Email }}            — user's email address
  {{ .NewEmail }}         — new email (for email change confirmation)
  {{ .RedirectTo }}       — the redirect URL passed with the auth call
```

### Common template bugs

```html
<!-- BUG: Using {{ .ConfirmationURL }} for magic link / OTP login -->
<!-- This sends a link — but if you're using OTP flow, user expects a CODE -->
<p>Your code is: {{ .ConfirmationURL }}</p>  <!-- WRONG — shows a URL not a code -->

<!-- CORRECT for OTP flow -->
<p>Your login code is: <strong>{{ .Token }}</strong></p>
<p>This code expires in 10 minutes.</p>

<!-- CORRECT for magic link / confirm email flow -->
<p><a href="{{ .ConfirmationURL }}">Confirm your email</a></p>

<!-- BUG: Hardcoding your domain — breaks staging/preview URLs -->
<a href="https://myapp.com/confirm?token={{ .Token }}">Confirm</a>  <!-- WRONG -->

<!-- CORRECT — use SiteURL variable -->
<a href="{{ .SiteURL }}/auth/callback?token_hash={{ .TokenHash }}&type=email">Confirm</a>
```

### Minimal working email template
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 600px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 0 20px;">
  <h2>{{ if eq .Type "signup" }}Confirm your email{{ else if eq .Type "recovery" }}Reset your password{{ else }}Sign in{{ end }}</h2>

  {{ if .Token }}
    <p>Your verification code:</p>
    <div style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: bold; letter-spacing: 8px; margin: 20px 0;">
      {{ .Token }}
    </div>
    <p style="color: #666;">This code expires in 10 minutes.</p>
  {{ else }}
    <p><a href="{{ .ConfirmationURL }}"
       style="background: #1a1a1a; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 6px; display: inline-block;">
      Click to confirm
    </a></p>
  {{ end }}

  <p style="color: #999; font-size: 13px;">If you didn't request this, you can ignore this email.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

