## Redirect URLs — Wildcards and Common Mistakes

```
Dashboard → Auth → URL Configuration

Site URL: https://yourdomain.com
(Used as the base for relative redirects and email template {{ .SiteURL }})

Redirect URLs — must add ALL of these for typical Rocket project:
  http://localhost:3000/**
  https://yourdomain.com/**
  https://*.netlify.app/**        ← wildcard for Netlify preview deploys
  https://yourdomain.netlify.app/**
```

### Wildcard syntax
```
*        — matches any single path segment (no slashes)
**       — matches any path including slashes (use this for most cases)

Examples:
  https://myapp.netlify.app/**  → matches any path on this domain
  https://*.netlify.app/**      → matches ANY Netlify subdomain (all preview deploys)
  https://myapp.com/**          → matches any path on custom domain
```

### Why OAuth breaks on deploy (and how to fix it)
```
Symptom: OAuth works on localhost, fails after Netlify deploy
Cause:   redirect URL mismatch — the callback URL is not in the allowed list

Fix checklist:
1. Add https://yourdomain.netlify.app/auth/callback to redirect URLs
2. Add https://*.netlify.app/** for preview deploy support
3. Set Site URL to your production domain (not localhost)
4. Check the redirectTo option in signInWithOAuth() matches exactly
```

```typescript
// Always use window.location.origin for the redirectTo — adapts to any environment
const { error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth({
  provider: 'google',
  options: {
    redirectTo: `${window.location.origin}/auth/callback`,
    // Do NOT hardcode: redirectTo: 'https://myapp.com/auth/callback'
    // It breaks on localhost and preview URLs
  },
})
```

