## Password Security

### Strength settings
```
Dashboard → Auth → Settings → Password → Minimum password length (default: 6)
Dashboard → Auth → Settings → Password → Required characters (lowercase, uppercase, digits, symbols)
```

### HaveIBeenPwned breach detection (Pro plan)
```
Dashboard → Auth → Settings → Password → Check for leaked passwords → Enable

When enabled: Supabase checks new passwords against HaveIBeenPwned.org database
If password found in breach data → rejected with WeakPasswordError
User sees: "This password has been found in a data breach. Please choose a different password."
```

### Handle WeakPasswordError in your code
```typescript
import { AuthWeakPasswordError } from '@supabase/supabase-js'

const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signUp({ email, password })

if (error instanceof AuthWeakPasswordError) {
  // error.message tells you WHY it's weak
  // error.reasons is an array: ['characters', 'leaked', 'length']
  const reasons = error.reasons ?? []

  if (reasons.includes('leaked')) {
    setError('This password has appeared in a data breach. Please choose another.')
  } else if (reasons.includes('length')) {
    setError(`Password must be at least ${error.status} characters.`)
  } else if (reasons.includes('characters')) {
    setError('Password must include uppercase, lowercase, a number, and a symbol.')
  } else {
    setError(error.message)
  }
  return
}
```

