## Custom SMTP — Stop Auth Emails Going to Spam

Default Supabase emails come from `noreply@mail.supabase.io` — treated as spam by most email clients. Every production project must configure custom SMTP.

### Setup with Resend (recommended — most Rocket projects already have Resend)
```
1. Resend Dashboard → Domains → Add Domain → verify your domain
2. Resend Dashboard → API Keys → Create API Key → copy it
3. Resend SMTP credentials:
   Host:     smtp.resend.com
   Port:     465 (SSL) or 587 (TLS)
   Username: resend
   Password: [your Resend API key]
   Sender:   noreply@yourdomain.com

4. Supabase Dashboard → Auth → SMTP Settings → Enable Custom SMTP
   Fill in the above credentials
   Sender email: noreply@yourdomain.com
   Sender name:  [Your App Name]

5. Test: Auth → SMTP → Send test email
```

### Common SMTP errors
```
"535 Authentication failed" → wrong API key or username is not "resend"
"550 Sender not verified" → domain not verified in Resend dashboard
"Connection timeout" → wrong port (try 587 if 465 fails)
Emails still not arriving → check Resend dashboard → Logs for delivery status
```

