## Auth Audit Logs — Diagnose Auth Failures

```
Supabase Dashboard → Auth → Logs

Events logged:
  user.signed_in         — successful sign in (with provider)
  user.signed_out        — sign out
  user.signed_up         — new user registration
  token.refreshed        — access token silently refreshed
  user.password_recovery — password reset link clicked
  user.email_change      — email changed
  user.updated           — user metadata updated
  mfa.challenge_verified — MFA code verified
  mfa.factor_added       — new MFA factor enrolled
```

```
Using logs to diagnose "user says they can't log in":
1. Filter by user email
2. Look for sign_in events → check for failure events before them
3. Check if email_not_confirmed error appears
4. Check for rate limit events (too many failed attempts)
5. Check timestamp of last token.refreshed — if old, session expired naturally
```

